 1️⃣ Function Declaration
   
A Function Declaration is a standard function defined using the function keyword and 
it can be called before its declaration due to hoisting.
	
function add(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}
let result = add(2, 3);
console.log(result);


2️⃣ Function Expression

Hinglish:
Function Expression me function ko ek variable me store kiya jata hai aur ise call karne se pehle define karna zaroori hota hai.

English:
A Function Expression is a function stored inside a variable and it must be defined before calling it.

const add = function(a, b) {
  return a + b;
};

let result = add(5, 4);
console.log(result);

3️⃣ Arrow Function

English:

Arrow Function was introduced in ES6 and provides a shorter syntax, and its this behavior is different from regular functions.

const add = (a, b) => {
  return a + b;
};

let result = add(10, 5);
console.log(result);


4️⃣ Anonymous Function

English:
An Anonymous Function is a function without a name and it is usually used as a callback.

const greet = function( str ) {
	console.log("Welcome to ", str);
};
    
greet("GeeksforGeeks!");


5️⃣ IIFE (Immediately Invoked Function)

English:
IIFE is a function that runs immediately after it is defined

(function () {
  console.log("IIFE function run ho gaya");
})();


6️⃣ Callback Function

English:
A Callback Function is a function passed as an argument to another function and executed later.

function greet(name, callback) {
  console.log("Hello " + name);
  callback();
}

function bye() {
  console.log("Bye Yashu");
}

greet("Yashu", bye);


7️⃣ Constructor Function

English:
A Constructor Function is used to create objects and it is called using the new keyword.

function Person(name, age) {
  this.name = name;
  this.age = age;
}

const p1 = new Person("Yashu", 21);
console.log(p1.name);
console.log(p1.age);


